review_blob: Dark brown with reddish tint, smooth and enjoyable. Will try other beers from this brewer.

I bought this on a whim, Liked the upfront taste and didnt mind its hoppiness but didnt care for the finish.
Didnt know anything about this beer until I opened it up. I dont care for these types of beer overall.

I opened this one on Halloween. This was the second pumpkin beer I have tried. Good aroma, flavor was decent but I am still looking for one that really reminds me of pumpkin pie. The spices were evident.
Black, chocolate, really warming. I enjoyed this beer. Its in short supply where I live so I picked up a few without tasting. Glad I did cause Id like to be able to keep this in my on hand supply.
I am not a fan of IPAs and this one proved it for me not that it is a bad beer but not for my palate. If you like bitter, hoppy beers this ones for you.
Very dark. One of my favorite beers. Always a cold one in the fridge. The smoke aroma and taste is what does it. Very easy to drink.
Dark smooth beer, a little light in the aroma department but very easy to drink for a stout. One of my favorites to have on hand.
Very dark and creamy. A great beer for coffee lovers and beer lovers alike. Very easy drinker.
beer_name: Midnight Sun Arctic Rhino Coffee Porter
